tly has to do with the cooperation/teaming aspect they are trying to promote. <P>I personally have never had a problem getting a bind, but I have many friedns and guild members who are more than happy to oblidge.<P>------------------<BR>Blackivar the Cunning<BR>Halfling Rogue<BR>19th Season<BR>Druzzil Ro Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ancaglon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm pretty sure there's an item that drops in Karnor's Castle with 1 charge of Bind Affinity. The Ring of the Dead (from the Thex Mallet Quest in Befallen/Neriak) used to have 1 charge of this too, but it was pulled.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shadowbound</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">And, while we're at it... how about a staff that ports your group to a Wizard Spire? And these can be used by everybody... oh, and I wouldn't mind a Ring that could Complete Heal me... y'know, just for those emergencies.<P>As convenient, and wonderous as these items may be... challenge should -never- be taken from this game. If you want to Bind, be a caster. SoW? Be a Shaman, or Druid. A class simply can't have it all... which is why they have their strengths and weaknesses.<P>X---X<BR>Vindayil, 14th Season Binder<BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SolClaryn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I can't count the times I have heard, from Verant in its MANY forms(GMS and so forth) that this is a GROUP game, you are GOING to group, and that means someone who can SOW and someone who can bind. I understand FULLY your frustration, I have had Groups from HELL, total party wipeouts and so forth. Most of the time I SOLO and there is a SERIOUS reason behind it, most KIDS(yes yall under the real life age of 21 ARE kids!!) are impatient, self absorbed and inconciderate. They can TRY to work on those bad tendancies BUT that is part of being 13 to 21, just as the over blown sex drive and zits, you can change it just not THAT much.<BR>  I would be in HEAVEN if more adults were playing and if more of them were willing to be HONEST about being adult.<BR>  I don't charge for a bind, and I try to be aware of when the boat comes in(warriors WILL be on that boat and NEED a bind). And if I am NOT on my way through zone to get to hunt I WILL stop to bind a handful of them.<BR>  What I would like to see more of is LOW level items(UNDER and WAY under level 25) that improve vision. How about a stone that is LOOTED that can be used in jewel crafting, that makes a PERMANENT vision mask, maybe with gold and plat some AC or other bonus and ULTRA(dark elf) vision. Just a thought.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
